Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows persistent hypercholesterolemia and hypertriglyceridemia, with elevated LDL cholesterol, increasing cardiovascular risk. There is also mild hypercreatininemia, suggesting possible renal impairment, and mild hyperkalemia. Albumin is slightly elevated, and ALT is mildly increased, which may indicate mild liver involvement. Other parameters are within normal limits. Clinical correlation and further evaluation of renal and hepatic function are recommended.
